## Design notes worth remembering

- Almost everything is **`static inline` in headers** → one TU (`dumpexe.cpp`), simple but will get heavy as the RE pipeline grows.
- Global CPU registers in `registers.h` are process-wide; fine for CLI, awkward if you later want multi-threaded or multi-image analysis.
- EXE sim uses `DS/ES = loadBase` (image base); COM uses all segs = load segment, `IP=0100h`, `SP=FFFE` — correct DOS model.
- `examples/output_help.txt` is slightly **stale** vs current CLI (missing COM/SYS, `-n`, `--psp`).
- Capstone is available on this machine; project builds should work after `make`.

