## Assistant

Yes — **CGA**, and specifically **40-column color text mode**, not a graphics mode like 320×200.

## What the game asks for

Strings in `ICON.EXE`:

- *“You must be using the **Color Graphics** Adapter…”*
- *“…compatible with a **color graphics card**.”*
- *“Insert your DOS disk and type **`MODE CO40`**”*

`MODE CO40` is the classic DOS command for **40×25 color text** on CGA.

README also says it draws in **hybrid text mode** with a **custom 8×8 font** (so tiles/sprites look like “graphics” but sit in the text-mode frame buffer).

## What the code actually sets

INT 10h **AH=00** (set video mode) shows up with **AL=01h** (several sites, e.g. patterns like `B8 01 00 CD 10` = `mov ax,0001h` / `int 10h`).

| Mode | Meaning (BIOS) |
|------|----------------|
| **01h** | **40×25 text, 16 colors** — **CGA** |
| 00h | 40×25 text, mono (sometimes used transiently; sim also saw mode 00) |

Other INT 10h usage matches **text-mode** work, not EGA/VGA graphics:

| AH | Typical use |
|----|-------------|
| 02h | Set cursor |
| 03h | Get cursor |
| 05h | Set active display page |
| 09h | Write char+attr |
| 0Bh | Palette / border |
| 0Fh | Get current mode |
| 11h | Character generator (load custom font) — fits custom 8×8 set |

No evidence of modes like **04h/06h** (CGA bitmap), **0Dh/0Eh/10h** (EGA), or **13h** (VGA).

## Bottom line

| Question | Answer |
|----------|--------|
| CGA? | **Yes** (Color Graphics Adapter required) |
| Mode? | **BIOS mode 01h = 40×25 16-color text** (`MODE CO40`) |
| How does art work? | **Text-mode / hybrid**: custom font + char/attribute cells (often B800), not full bitmap CGA |
| EGA/VGA native? | **No** (only as CGA-compatible text) |

So for DOSBox: CGA machine / CGA emulation and **40-column color text** is the right target; map RE as **character grid + attributes** is more likely than a 320×200 framebuffer.

