Yes — **mode `01h`** is the play mode (40×25 color text). Menus use **`03h`**. Both use the **color text** aperture, not A000 graphics.

### What the dump must record

| Field | Mode `01h` (play) | Mode `03h` (menus) |
|--------|-------------------|---------------------|
| BIOS mode | `0x01` | `0x03` |
| Phys base | **`0xB8000`** (`B800:0000`) | same |
| Visible size | **`0x7D0`** (40×25×2) | **`0xFA0`** (80×25×2) |
| Layout | `char, attr` words | same |
| Mono note | mode `07h` would be `B000:0000` — not ICON play | |

CGA/VGA still has **16 KiB** at `B8000`, but for RE you almost always want the **active page** (2000 or 4000 bytes), not the whole 16K unless you’re chasing page-flipping.

